87.question: How better is accuracy of new model compared to previously reported models?
87.response: {'Answer': 'The accuracy of the new PRN model is better compared to previously reported models in both single-task and multi-task training. In single-task training, PRN achieves the highest average accuracy (57.57) and performs best in the cloze (56.31) and ordering (62.77) tasks. In multi-task training, PRN shows a balanced performance, particularly in the coherence and ordering tasks, scoring 50.17 overall.'}
